Grigoriy Andreevich Rechkalov (Russian: Григо?рий Андре?евич Речка?лов; February 9, 1920 – December 20, 1990) was a fighter pilot for the Soviet Union during World War II. He was made a Hero of the Soviet Union on two separate occasions (24 May 1943 and 1 July 1944). He scored 56 confirmed personal victories and 6 additional shared victories in air combat. He is the second highest scoring Soviet pilot in World War II.
